Supermax: Rubber glove spot prices on downtrend  falling 15% to 25%1. As more new capacities are available in the market  rubber glove prices have started falling  said Supermax Corp Bhd.2. There have been more new glove players jumping on the bandwagon in view of the surge in demand. In addition  the current players are increasing capacities in a large scale  especially players who are public-listed companies based in China  Malaysia and Thailand  Supermax commented.3.  Supermax announced a quarterly net profit of RM1 billion for 3QFY21  5.2% lower compared with RM1.06 billion recorded in 2QFY21. Its quarter revenue fell 3% to RM1.94 billion in 3QFY21 compared with RM2 billion in 2QFY21. Supermax declared a special dividend of 13 sen per share.
